# TODO: mutual recursion with match body — wat succeeds but the
# output fails wasmtime validation at link time:
#   `type mismatch: expected funcref, found anyref`
# inside one of the hoisted fns (the struct.new $Closure is given an
# anyref param where a funcref is required). Culprit is emit/collect
# not registering every hoisted fn as a sibling func, so
# emit_get_raw_funcref falls through to local.get. Ping/pong above
# works. Snapshot here is the current (broken) output, blessed to
# make the regression visible when the fix lands.
